##Wuhan new pneumonia four types of personnel concentrated isolation, why so difficult?

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* In order to prevent cross-infection caused by home quarantine and control the source of infection, Wuhan began to focus on the treatment and isolation of confirmed, suspected, Febrile and close contacts.
* It is difficult to persuade people to go to the isolation point during the execution of the quarantine. They expect to be able to treat patients, or form a green channel for hospital testing and treatment.
* Han has opened more than 8,000 beds for new pneumonia patients, and with the opening of Vulcan Mountain, Thor Mountain and more designated hospitals, more than 10,000 beds will be opened in the near future.
* Outside the plan to build 11"Shelter Hospital" , provide beds tens of thousands of patients admitted with mild illness.
* In the treatment and isolation, block the source of infection of the difficult problem, see the hope of solution.

In order to prevent cross-infection caused by home quarantine and control the source of infection, Wuhan began to focus on the treatment and isolation of confirmed, suspected, fever and close contacts.

In practice, it was difficult to persuade personnel to go to the quarantines. They expect to be able to treat patients, or form a green channel for hospital testing and treatment.

Wuhan currently has more than 8,000 beds open for new pneumonia patients. With the opening of Huoshenshan, Raytheon and more designated hospitals, more than 10,000 beds can be opened in the near future.

In addition, 11"shelter hospitals" will be built to provide tens of thousands of beds for patients with mild illness.

Centralized treatment and isolation, block the source of infection of the problem, see the hope for a solution.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 3, quarantine hotel entrance, suspected patients ask the staff of the current isolation. Photo by Wu Jing.

On the afternoon of Feb. 3, a middle aged woman in her 40s, wearing a face mask, was talking on the phone outside a four star hotel in Gasp. A few workers in protective clothing at the door looked at her from a distance, afraid to come forward.

"You should have sent me to the hospital for treatment. Did you leave me here to die? " She barked at the community worker on the phone as she stood on the side of the road in front of the hotel, clutching a pile of laundry and CT scans, "I'm so sick that I have to be dragged here for observation? I'll be on oxygen at night. Nothing. I'll be dead, won't I? "

She was diagnosed with double Yang after a nucleic acid test. After saying a few words, she felt sick in her throat and immediately waved her hand to those around her. Then he coughed for a while, a little out of breath. She's waiting for her husband to pick her up.

It was the second day of Wuhan's "four categories" of people with confirmed, suspected, Febrile and close contacts, under a policy of intensive care and isolation.

Before this, these four categories of personnel are to let the community worker supervise them"home segregation". In just two weeks, more than 8,000 new cases of pneumonia have been confirmed in Wuhan, and more than 10,000 suspected cases have already been reported, suggesting that home isolation has proved difficult to stop the infection.

Internal family isolation and inadequate protective measures often infect more than one member of a family. Community workers can not bear the burden, in addition to the staff masks, protective clothing and other materials are seriously inadequate, the task of house-to-house investigation is difficult to complete. Telephone screening can not prevent some suspected patients and confirmed patients are still out of the home, forming a huge potential cross-infection.

It's very dangerous to isolate a confirmed or suspected patient at home, Zhong Nanshan said in an interview. VIDEO: CCTV  

In order to prevent the inevitable cross-contamination from home quarantine and control the source of infection, on February 2, the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Command requested that all districts, starting from today, measures have been taken to collect, treat and isolate the "four categories of people" who are involved in the new coronary pneumonia: unconditionally centralize the treatment of confirmed patients and arrange beds as soon as possible; centralize the isolation of suspected patients and requisition a group of private hospitals, equipped with the necessary living, disinfection, medical facilities, the fastest time to arrange testing; fever patients with centralized isolation observation; close contacts of centralized isolation.

The communities now have clear norms to enforce, but even so, persuading four categories of people to move from their homes to the quarantines remains difficult. While confirmed patients wish to be transferred to a hospital for admission, the other three groups of patients are either concerned about the limited isolation conditions at the isolation sites and the re-emergence of cross-infection, or are worried about family members who remain at home.

The criteria for the temporary requisition of hotel isolation points within a few days vary. Some have isolated only those in close contact; others have placed confirmed, highly suspected and close contacts on different floors in a single isolation point; some have deployed a small number of medical staff to provide medication for patients with mild illness; Some are not equipped with medical personnel and medication.

But for almost all types of patients, there is a common expectation at the point of separation: that they can be treated, or that they can form a green channel for checking in and seeing a doctor.

To meet such expectations, more beds are needed.

Of the patients and their families

On the afternoon of Feb. 3, the Woman's street sent a car to take her to the hotel, and she was excited at first, the excitement taking the place of the hopelessness of admission. For her, there was no longer the daily fear that her husband would be infected. It was an invisible bomb that had been buried in the house.

When checking in, she threw all her doubts to the front desk of the hotel and was told that there was no medicine, no oxygen machine, no medical equipment, and several doctors and thermometers had come here for isolation and observation, it's not a treatment -- it's not like a community worker told her, "there are health workers and medical practices in quarantine. ".

At this time, more and more people poured into the hotel. Police cars and street cars came to pick people up one after another. There was a long line at the door. There were confirmed patients and suspected patients. They were isolated on different floors of the hotel. Five floors were suspected patients, floors 10 through 11 are confirmed patients. The 160 or so beds were nearly full in just two days.

Like the woman, several confirmed patients slowly emerged from the quarantine, and the staff at the door could block family members and reporters who wanted to visit, but could not block the labored, slow-paced patients, i watched them come out one by one. Patients who have been diagnosed, even those with mild illnesses who need to be quarantined and hospitalized, want to be hospitalized and treated, not quarantined.

On the morning of Feb. 2, community workers called Zhang to report his parents'names and persuade him to send them to a quarantine site, where they had a highly suspected case of coronary pneumonia on a CT scan but had not yet had a nucleic acid test.

More than half an hour of persuasion process, Zhang Teng has been asking, isolated people can do nucleic acid testing? If the diagnosis is positive, can you arrange hospitalization? Staff were less certain that "the quarantines are where the nucleic acid tests are done, " but his parents would not be able to do the tests until two or three days after the names of those quarantined were reported to the hospital.

Staff said it was possible to report his parents as "critically ill, " in which case they could be quarantined at home, but that "the nucleic acid test would take a little longer. ".

Zhang Teng learned that the current waiting in the hospital for nucleic acid testing and community workers promised to focus on isolating the crowd for testing time is almost the same. For example, the Seventh Hospital of Wuhan is 2-3 days, the central South Hospital of Wuhan is 3-4 days. And, when heard that the quarantine point no medical staff, can not take medicine injection, after repeated weighing, Zhang Teng rejected the community's request.

At 8:00 that night, Zhang sent a message from the Wuchang Hospital he had contacted, telling him that the next morning, his family could go for a nucleic acid test.

That night, at his repeated request, the community sent a car to take his parents to the hospital in advance of the queue. He wheeled food and blankets on a shared bike for more than an hour to his parents, who waited in line all night. The next morning, his mother, who had lung infections, took a nucleic acid test. The results weren't in yet, the father with a one lung infection didn't qualify for a nucleic acid test, so he didn't.

At the same time, the community still called to persuade to quarantine, considering the quarantine point there is no medicine and medical staff, Zhang Teng finally refused.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Suspected and confirmed patients are queued up in isolated hotels for check-in. Photo by Wu Jing.

The community's problem

All four groups are segregated to varying degrees, which is no small challenge for the more than 2,000 communities in Wuhan. This test different communities in the previous ten days, the four groups of tracking is timely and in place. Determining whether a patient is mildly or severely ill, moving to a different isolation facility, and how to persuade a patient to agree to quarantine are all things that community workers need to think about.

After the policy was issued, community workers were, in principle, given only one day to persuade residents. The implementation process was not smooth, and some community workers were turned away, again sparking dissatisfaction among some patients because of the different standards of isolation in different regions.

According to the eight o'clock health news, many communities were not able to quickly isolate the four groups of people so quickly. Some streets simply did not differentiate according to the severity of the disease. Those who were diagnosed were reported to the streets for admission; those who were suspected and close contacts, are being quarantined at the hotel. In some streets, groups of four were so large that suspected and Febrile patients were isolated from confirmed and close contacts. Some communities, confirmed patients can not be arranged to stay in hospital, simply have been quarantined to hotels.

On the night of the announcement, a community secretary, Wang Yangming (not his real name) , was summoned to a meeting of the street administration. February 2 night before 12 o'clock, all confirmed patients to "zero, " that is, to report to the street manager, the street open hospital receipt, and all confirmed patients to the hospital. Those in close contact with the confirmed cases were quarantined at a nearby hotel for 14 days. But there was no mention of what to do with suspected patients and feverish residents.

"It's because I really can't take care of it. ". Wang Yangming says she doesn't even know how many people have fever. She could not be sure whether residents would lie about their fever, given that the community worker's protective clothing was not plentiful and that calls had been used instead of house calls.

Moreover, street managers have a clear definition of a "close contact" : a person who eats, lives, shares a car or works in an office with a confirmed patient must be a Shuangyang District patient who has been tested for nucleic acid.

After the meeting, Wang Yangming and her colleagues called the families of each confirmed patient one by one, urging them to pack up the next day and go to a nearby hotel, arranged by the street and free of charge. The next morning, again called the past, all the family members of the confirmed patients refused, the reason is not assured that the patient at home, the community first arranged on the family members admitted to say. And the community nearby designated hospitals, already overcrowded, a bed is hard to get, community workers can not make any commitment to their admission or not.

By Feb. 3, the number of confirmed cases in the Wang Yangming community was climbing, but no close contacts were persuaded to go to a hotel.

This is an extremely real-world problem, and it is not easy to isolate close family members in centralized isolation without resolving the issue of hospitalization. As for the quarantined hotel staffing, at one of the quarantine sites in Hanyang District, there are currently 24 close contacts with a doctor and a nurse, CCTV news reported.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Police transport suspected patients to quarantine hotel. Photo by Wu Jing.

Different types of people with different powers of persuasion

Some communities start with highly suspected patients and plan to quarantine them while they wait for nucleic acid tests.

On the morning of Feb. 4, Wang Qin, a resident of a Qiaokou District community, received a phone call from her parents'community worker, who told her that if her parents agreed to quarantine at a hotel, they would soon be able to arrange a nucleic acid test instead of waiting in line at a hospital, once diagnosed, there's a chance of hospitalization.

Wang's father developed a fever on Jan. 25. To prevent infection, Wang took his daughter to another home in Wuhan, where the parents were isolated. Father 28 CT examination, is highly suspected, took medicine home to eat, but since then has been repeated fever. On Feb. 2, He went back to the hospital for a CT scan. His lung infection was worse than the last time, but he couldn't get a nucleic acid test, meaning he would have to wait a long time to leave the hospital. During this time, my mother also caught pneumonia.

"You can either stay at home or you can go to a hotel, and you can have all the nucleic acid tests, but when, I don't know. ". The other side was straightforward.

After much deliberation, Wang decided not to go to a quarantined hotel, where medication and injections were not available and his father had to go to the hospital for injections every other day.

Another highly-suspected patient, who lives in the Qiaokou District area, was temporarily admitted to the isolation hotel on the afternoon of February 2, only to discover that the isolation hotel had not prepared the usual treatment drugs such as fever medicine.

Some communities recognize that it is not easy to persuade highly suspected patients to be quarantined in the first place, and that it involves real dilemmas that follow up services such as medication and injections are difficult to achieve. The community workers simply changed tactics, persuading a more isolated group of people to become close contacts.

She lives in Zhang Yang, Hanyang District, and her parents are highly suspicious. On the morning of February 2, when the community called to ask if Zhang Yang would be willing to quarantine the suspected patients to prevent their spread, Zhang Yang agreed, thinking it would be a good thing to cut off the source of infection and provide food and shelter for the parents.

That night, the community again called, let immediately pack up, drive parents to quarantine hotel, drop a word, in can not casually out.

Zhang Yang suddenly realized that her parents still had to do a review. What was the arrangement? Parents who suddenly get sicker, they have breathing support? Parents still have to renew medicine, how to do? The community was stumped, and the response was, no. Finally, Zhang Yang refused.

But the next day, things changed. Zhang Yang's father got the results of the nucleic acid test, which turned out to be positive, from a suspected patient to a confirmed one. At this point, the community's strategy was temporarily adjusted: Instead of persuading Zhang Yang's parents, it persuaded him to sequester himself -- from a highly suspected population to close contacts.

When the community workers made it possible to arrange hospital beds for Zhang Yang's father, Zhang Yang was tempted. On the afternoon of February 3, Zhang Yang decided to go into quarantine.

In the evening, he was arranged by the street car received the hotel, check-in, the front desk pulled him into the "XX close observation point of personnel" group, within two days, the group quickly added more than 60 people.

Hotel Room is a person, the owner of the group told, no special circumstances not to go out, even out of the room door is not okay. The Three Meals a Day will arrive at the door on time, wearing a mask and opening the door to get their food.

However, the quarantined hotel was requisitioned temporarily. The hotel does not have a waiter. At present, there are only four doctors and nurses working part-time as waiters. "The previous price was 5,000 yuan for seven days, and no one could be found! " The group owner said in the group, so we can only provide the most basic services.

For the next 14 days, Zhang Yang will move around the 20 square meter space, taking his temperature twice a day. If fever is found, the hotel will arrange a green channel to the fever clinic.

"If my parents were in a bad way and had a knife to my throat, I wouldn't dare come, but at least they're on their own for now. ". His only hope now was that the community would deliver on its promise of a bed for his father.

Vulcan Mountain, Thor Mountain, Shelter Hospital

More beds are the answer

Beds are a problem.

A patient who had been admitted to Wuhan's Fifth Hospital on January 23 was still not admitted to the upper-tier hospital after more than 10 days.

In one Jianghan District community there were 10 confirmed cases, and the streets could not admit any of them because hospital beds were so tight.

One of the patients was cured, by waiting in line, and the other three, by applying for admission in their own right.

A resident's in-laws died on January 29th and 31st after being diagnosed with a highly suspected case of coronavirus pneumonia. She called the street countless times, and the street told them to call 120 themselves. After the death of their parents-in-law, the couple became close family members, immersed in the grief of the loss of their loved ones because of distrust of the streets and the community and a strong resistance to centralized segregation.

"NUCLEIC ACID testing is easier now than before, " said a community worker. "Some hospitals have opened up testing channels in outpatient clinics, but once patients are diagnosed, there are still no beds. "

Yesterday, the 1000-bed Huoshenshan hospital has received the first batch of patients, today, the Leishenshan hospital will also be completed, 1600 beds will soon open, and Wuhan Designated Hospital is also being opened in batches, recently added more than 2000 beds.

According to data released by Wuhan Health Commission, as of 23:00 on February 3,2020,28 designated hospitals in Wuhan had a total of 8,199 beds open, including the first batch of 50 beds received by Huoshenshan.

In addition, on February 3, Wuhan urgently built a "shelter hospital" in the Wembley Arena, the Wuhan Living Room, and the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center, adding 3,400 beds to admit and treat patients with mild illness and maintain the channel of severe cases for referral.

Visit "Shelter Hospital" , video source: Red Star Video

"Shelter Hospital" is a kind of PLA field mobile medical system, built by a number of mobile modules, these modules can be real houses, tents and other temporary accommodation. In exceptional cases, it serves as an emergency hospital. Has Participated in the Wenchuan County earthquake, 2010 Yushu earthquake and other emergency medical rescue missions.

Xinhua News Agency on the evening of 4 News, Wuhan "Shelter Hospital" to expand to 11, receiving more than 10,000 beds.

Four categories of personnel centralized treatment and isolation, cut off the source of infection of the problem, see the hope for a solution.
